President Uhuru Kenyatta and opposition leader Raila Odinga led thousands of mourners in honouring the late Kenneth Matiba in Murang'a on Thursday. Also in attendance were Deputy president William Ruto, Governor Mwangi wa Iria, Senator Irungu Kang'ata, Woman Representative Sabina Chege and area MP Ndindi Nyoro.  A member of the family of former Cabinet minister Kenneth Matiba carries his picture at Murang'a's Ihura Stadium during the funeral service on April 26, 2018. /ALICE WAITHERA  The coffin containing the body of former Cabinet minister Kenneth Matiba is moved, for a funeral service at Murang'a's Ihura Stadium, April 26, 2018. /ALICE WAITHERA Others were Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho, Kisumu's Anyang Nyong'o, Kiambu's Ferdinand Waituitu, Nairobi's Mike Sonko and Meru's Kiraitu Murungi and MInisters James Macharia (Roads), Mwangi Kiunjuri (Water) and Eugene Wamalwa (Devolution).  Murang'a Senator Irungu Kang'ata, Kandara MP Alice Wahome, Transport Cabinet Secretary James Macharia, Murang'a Governor Mwangi wa Iria and Bishop John Michuki at the funeral service for former Cabinet minister Kenneth Matiba at Ihura Stadium in Murang'a county, April 26, 2018. /ALICE WAITHERA  Kisumu Governor Anyang' Nyong'o at the funeral service for former Cabinet minister Kenneth Matiba at Ihura Stadium in Murang'a county, April 26, 2018. /ALICE WAITHERA  Water CS Mwangi Kiunjuri at the funeral service for former Cabinet minister Kenneth Matiba at Ihura Stadium in Murang'a county, April 26, 2018. /ALICE WAITHERA Matiba's second funeral service is taking place at Ihura Stadium ahead of his cremation on Friday. The first service took place at All Saints Cathedral in Nairobi on Wednesday. More on this: [Photos] Uhuru leads Kenyans in mourning Matiba at Nairobi service Also read: Matiba to be cremated as he wished Click here for the latest political news  